{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AgwsJsuego7RfwZsZzGD7k","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 14-1: Retro-to-Sprint Pipeline (Step 8b) + Persistent epic-TD\n     2→\n     3→## Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     8→\n     9→## Story\n    10→\n    11→As a developer running harness-run,\n    12→I want retro action items to auto-create stories under epic-TD,\n    13→So that tech debt gets tracked and prioritized automatically.\n    14→\n    15→## Acceptance Criteria\n    16→\n    17→1. Given a retro file with `### Fix Now` items, when `processRetroActionItems()` runs, then new `TD-N-slug: backlog` entries appear in sprint-state.json stories under `epic-TD` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→2. Given `epic-TD` doesn't exist in sprint-state.json, when the first TD story is created via `ensureEpicTd()`, then `epic-TD` is created with `status: 'in-progress'` and `storiesTotal: 1`, `storiesDone: 0` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→3. Given `epic-TD` already exists with 2 stories, when a new TD story is created, then `epic-TD.storiesTotal` is incremented to 3 and existing stories are preserved <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→4. Given a duplicate action item with 80%+ word overlap with an existing TD story title, when `processRetroActionItems()` processes it, then it is skipped and an `[INFO] Skipping duplicate` message is logged <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→5. Given a retro file with `### Fix Soon` items, when `processRetroActionItems()` runs, then those items also create `TD-N-slug: backlog` entries (same as Fix Now) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→6. Given a retro file with `### Backlog` items, when `processRetroActionItems()` runs, then those items are appended to `tech-debt-backlog.md` but do NOT create sprint-state stories <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→7. Given `generateSprintStatusYaml()` runs on a state with `epic-TD` stories, when the YAML is generated, then `epic-TD` status is always `in-progress` regardless of whether all TD stories are done <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→8. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→9. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→10. Given no new file created for this story, when line count is checked, then no modified file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→\n    28→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    29→\n    30→- [x] Task 1 (AC: 1, 5): Extend `src/lib/retro-parser.ts` with section-aware parsing\n    31→  - [x] Add `RetroSectionItem` interface with `section: 'fix-now' | 'fix-soon' | 'backlog'`, `text: string`\n    32→  - [x] Add `parseRetroSections(content: string): RetroSectionItem[]` that parses `## 6. Action Items` and its subsections\n    33→  - [x] Handle varying subsection header formats: `### Fix Now (Before Next Session)`, `### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)`, `#### Fix Now`, etc.\n    34→  - [x] Extract bullet items (`- ` or numbered `1. `) under each subsection\n    35→\n    36→- [x] Task 2 (AC: 4): Add deduplication logic\n    37→  - [x] Add `normalizeText(text: string): string[]` — lowercase, remove punctuation, split into words\n    38→  - [x] Add `wordOverlap(a: string[], b: string[]): number` — returns overlap percentage (0-1)\n    39→  - [x] Add `isDuplicate(newItem: string, existingTitles: string[], threshold?: number): { duplicate: boolean; matchedTitle?: string }` with default threshold 0.8\n    40→\n    41→- [x] Task 3 (AC: 2, 3): Add epic-TD management to `src/modules/sprint/state.ts`\n    42→  - [x] Add `ensureEpicTd(state: SprintState): SprintState` — creates `epic-TD` if absent, returns updated state\n    43→  - [x] Add `createTdStory(state: SprintState, slug: string): SprintState` — adds `TD-{N}-{slug}` story, increments `epic-TD.storiesTotal`\n    44→  - [x] Add `nextTdStoryNumber(state: SprintState): number` — scans existing `TD-*` story keys, returns max+1 (or 1 if none)\n    45→\n    46→- [x] Task 4 (AC: 7): Prevent epic-TD completion in YAML generation\n    47→  - [x] In `generateSprintStatusYaml()` in `state.ts`, add check: if epicKey is `'TD'`, force status to `'in-progress'` regardless of story statuses\n    48→\n    49→- [x] Task 5 (AC: 1, 5, 6): Create `src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts` orchestrator\n    50→  - [x] Add `processRetroActionItems(retroContent: string, state: SprintState): { updatedState: SprintState; created: string[]; skipped: string[]; backlogAppended: string[] }`\n    51→  - [x] For `fix-now` and `fix-soon` items: generate slug from item text, check dedup, call `createTdStory()`\n    52→  - [x] For `backlog` items: append to `tech-debt-backlog.md` file\n    53→  - [x] Return created/skipped/backlogAppended arrays for logging\n    54→\n    55→- [x] Task 6 (AC: 1, 5, 6, 4): Create `src/lib/__tests__/retro-to-sprint.test.ts`\n    56→  - [x] Test: Fix Now items create TD stories in state\n    57→  - [x] Test: Fix Soon items create TD stories in state\n    58→  - [x] Test: Backlog items do NOT create stories, append to file\n    59→  - [x] Test: Duplicate items (80%+ overlap) are skipped\n    60→  - [x] Test: Non-duplicate items (< 80% overlap) are created\n    61→  - [x] Test: epic-TD auto-created on first TD story\n    62→  - [x] Test: epic-TD.storiesTotal incremented on subsequent stories\n    63→  - [x] Test: TD story numbering auto-increments correctly\n    64→\n    65→- [x] Task 7 (AC: 4): Create `src/lib/__tests__/retro-parser-sections.test.ts`\n    66→  - [x] Test: Parses `### Fix Now` items from retro content\n    67→  - [x] Test: Parses `### Fix Soon` items from retro content\n    68→  - [x] Test: Parses `### Backlog` items from retro content\n    69→  - [x] Test: Handles varying header formats (with/without parenthetical suffixes)\n    70→  - [x] Test: Deduplication normalizeText and wordOverlap edge cases\n    71→\n    72→- [x] Task 8 (AC: 7): Add test for epic-TD YAML generation\n    73→  - [x] Test: `generateSprintStatusYaml()` always shows `epic-TD: in-progress` even when all TD stories are done\n    74→\n    75→- [x] Task 9 (AC: 8): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n    76→- [x] Task 10 (AC: 9): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n    77→- [x] Task 11 (AC: 10): Verify all modified/new files are under 300 lines\n    78→\n    79→## Dev Notes\n    80→\n    81→### Architecture Compliance\n    82→\n    83→- **Decision 6 (Retro-to-Sprint Pipeline):** This story implements the first two mechanisms from architecture-v3.md Decision 6: persistent epic-TD and retro-to-sprint auto-creation. The third mechanism (tech debt gate in story selection) is story 14-2.\n    84→- **Decision 7 (300-line limit, NFR5):** All new/modified files must stay under 300 lines.\n    85→\n    86→### Implementation Guidance\n    87→\n    88→#### Retro Section Parser\n    89→\n    90→The existing `parseRetroActionItems()` in `retro-parser.ts` parses table-format action items (the `| # | Action | Status | Notes |` table). This story adds a NEW function `parseRetroSections()` that parses the **subsection-based** action items format used in the `## 6. Action Items` section.\n    91→\n    92→Real retro files use varying header formats:\n    93→- `### Fix Now (Before Next Session)` or `#### Fix Now (Before Next Session)`\n    94→- `### Fix Soon (Next Sprint / Next Session)` or `### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)`\n    95→- `### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)` or `### Backlog (Escalated Priority)` or `### Backlog (Carry Forward)`\n    96→\n    97→Items under each subsection are bullet lists:\n    98→```markdown\n    99→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n   100→- Item one description here\n   101→- Item two description here\n   102→\n   103→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n   104→1. Another item here\n   105→2. Yet another item\n   106→```\n   107→\n   108→The parser should match headers case-insensitively and strip parenthetical suffixes to classify into `fix-now`, `fix-soon`, or `backlog`.\n   109→\n   110→#### TD Story Key Generation\n   111→\n   112→Story keys follow the pattern `TD-{N}-{slug}` where:\n   113→- `N` is auto-incremented (scan existing TD-* keys, take max number + 1)\n   114→- `slug` is derived from the item text: lowercase, replace non-alphanumeric with hyphens, truncate to 40 chars, trim trailing hyphens\n   115→\n   116→Example: \"Fix bare catch blocks in registry.ts\" → `TD-1-fix-bare-catch-blocks-in-registry-ts`\n   117→\n   118→#### Deduplication\n   119→\n   120→Normalize: lowercase, remove all punctuation (keep alphanumeric and spaces), split on whitespace.\n   121→Overlap = |intersection(a, b)| / min(|a|, |b|).\n   122→Using min rather than max prevents short items from being considered duplicates of unrelated long items.\n   123→\n   124→#### Epic-TD in State\n   125→\n   126→`epic-TD` is stored in `state.epics['epic-TD']` like any other epic. The key difference:\n   127→1. It is auto-created (not pre-defined in epics YAML)\n   128→2. Its status must NEVER be set to `done` — force `in-progress` in all paths\n   129→3. `generateSprintStatusYaml()` at line ~157 computes `const allDone = storyKeys.every(...)` — this must check `if (epicKey === 'TD') epicStatus = 'in-progress'` to override\n   130→\n   131→TD stories are stored in `state.stories` alongside regular stories. The `TD-` prefix distinguishes them. The `parseStoryKey()` function returns `[Infinity, Infinity]` for non-numeric prefixes, so TD stories will sort after all numeric-prefixed stories in YAML output. This is acceptable.\n   132→\n   133→#### Backlog File\n   134→\n   135→`tech-debt-backlog.md` lives at project root. Append items with timestamp:\n   136→```markdown\n   137→## Backlog Items (auto-appended from retros)\n   138→\n   139→- [2026-03-24] Item description here\n   140→```\n   141→\n   142→If the file doesn't exist, create it with the header.\n   143→\n   144→### Testing Guidance\n   145→\n   146→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n   147→- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'`\n   148→- Import convention: use `.js` extension for ESM resolution (e.g., `from '../retro-parser.js'`).\n   149→- Mock `writeFileSync` for backlog file append tests.\n   150→- Use fixture retro content strings — do NOT read real retro files in tests.\n   151→- Test deduplication with edge cases: exact match (100%), slight variation (85%), clearly different (30%), empty items.\n   152→\n   153→### Previous Story Intelligence (13-3)\n   154→\n   155→- Story 13-3 completed successfully. All tests passing.\n   156→- The `src/commands/run.ts` has been refactored to use the AgentDriver pattern.\n   157→- `src/lib/retro-parser.ts` currently has 123 lines — well within budget for extension.\n   158→- `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` currently has 525 lines — consider putting new TD functions in a separate file if they push it over 300 (it's already over). Recommendation: create `src/modules/sprint/td-state.ts` to keep functions isolated.\n   159→\n   160→### Key Observations About Existing Code\n   161→\n   162→1. **`generateSprintStatusYaml()`** (state.ts:122-169) computes epic status from stories at line 157. The epic-TD override must go here.\n   163→2. **`parseStoryKey()`** (state.ts:175-179) expects numeric prefixes — `TD-1-slug` will return `[Infinity, Infinity]`. This means TD stories will group under a single \"Infinity\" epic group in YAML. This needs a fix: add special-case handling for `TD-` prefix in `parseStoryKey()` or in `generateSprintStatusYaml()`.\n   164→3. **`state.ts` is already 525 lines** — over the 300-line limit. New functions MUST go in a new file (`src/modules/sprint/td-state.ts` or `src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts`).\n   165→4. **The retro parser's existing `parseRetroActionItems()`** parses the table format, not the subsection format. These are two different sections of the retro file. The new parser is additive.\n   166→\n   167→### Retro File Format Reference\n   168→\n   169→From real retro files (e.g., `session-retro-2026-03-24.md`):\n   170→```markdown\n   171→## 6. Action Items\n   172→\n   173→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n   174→- Fix bare catch blocks in registry.ts (line 73)\n   175→- Update init-project to persist multi-stacks\n   176→\n   177→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n   178→1. Add element type checking to isValidState()\n   179→2. Unit test recoverCorruptedState() recovery paths\n   180→\n   181→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n   182→- Remove StackDetection type duplication (deferred to 10-5)\n   183→- Address pre-existing TS compilation errors in test files\n   184→```\n   185→\n   186→### Project Structure After This Story\n   187→\n   188→```\n   189→src/lib/\n   190→├── retro-parser.ts          # Extended with parseRetroSections(), normalizeText(), wordOverlap()\n   191→├── retro-to-sprint.ts       # NEW: processRetroActionItems() orchestrator\n   192→├── __tests__/\n   193→│   ├── retro-parser-sections.test.ts  # NEW: section parsing + dedup tests\n   194→│   └── retro-to-sprint.test.ts        # NEW: integration tests for TD story creation\n   195→src/modules/sprint/\n   196→├── state.ts                 # Modified: epic-TD override in generateSprintStatusYaml()\n   197→```\n   198→\n   199→### References\n   200→\n   201→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md lines 313-331] — Story 14-1 epic definition\n   202→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md] — Decision 6 (Retro-to-Sprint Pipeline)\n   203→- [Source: src/lib/retro-parser.ts] — Existing retro parser (table format)\n   204→- [Source: src/modules/sprint/state.ts lines 122-169] — generateSprintStatusYaml() to modify\n   205→- [Source: src/modules/sprint/state.ts lines 175-179] — parseStoryKey() limitation with non-numeric prefixes\n   206→\n   207→## Files to Change\n   208→\n   209→- `src/lib/retro-parser.ts` — Add `parseRetroSections()`, `normalizeText()`, `wordOverlap()`, `isDuplicate()` functions\n   210→- `src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts` — NEW: `processRetroActionItems()` orchestrator, slug generation, backlog file append\n   211→- `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` — Modify `generateSprintStatusYaml()` to force epic-TD status to in-progress; fix `parseStoryKey()` for TD- prefix\n   212→- `src/lib/__tests__/retro-parser-sections.test.ts` — NEW: Tests for section parsing and deduplication\n   213→- `src/lib/__tests__/retro-to-sprint.test.ts` — NEW: Tests for TD story creation orchestration\n   214→\n   215→## Change Log\n   216→\n   217→- 2026-03-24: Story created from epic definition with 3 ACs, expanded to 10 ACs with full task breakdown, verification tags, and dev notes. Status set to ready-for-dev.\n   218→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QdekhbhdCn1yMfA8HwX61q","session_id":"84a01a9c-e466-45b4-91ef-8201b3712d8d","uuid":"f6264a6e-f280-45dc-b53b-7d2546c414db","timestamp":"2026-03-24T21:56:40.726Z"}
