{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QdekhbhdCn1yMfA8HwX61q","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td.md\n**Issues Found:** 3 High, 1 Medium, 2 Low\n**Issues Fixed:** 3 High, 1 Medium\n**Tests Added:** 4 new tests (3657 total, all passing)\n**Coverage:** 97.1% overall, all 154 files above 80% per-file floor\n**Story Status:** verifying\n\n### HIGH Issues (all fixed)\n\n1. **H1 - `generateSlug` returns empty string for punctuation-only input** (`src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts:24-31`). Creates malformed story keys like `TD-1-` that break `nextTdStoryNumber` regex matching. **Fixed:** returns `'untitled'` as fallback.\n\n2. **H2 - `processRetroActionItems` reports `backlogAppended` items when no file was written** (`src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts:167`). When `projectRoot` is omitted, backlog items are added to the result array but never persisted. Callers believe items were appended when they weren't. **Fixed:** clears `backlogAppended` when `projectRoot` is absent.\n\n3. **H3 - `wordOverlap` returns values >1.0 with duplicate words** (`src/lib/retro-parser.ts:214-219`). Input like `['fix','fix','fix']` vs `['fix']` yielded overlap=3.0 because `filter` counted duplicates against a Set. This breaks the 0-1 contract and makes deduplication unreliable. **Fixed:** use Set on both sides before computing intersection.\n\n### MEDIUM Issues (fixed)\n\n1. **M1 - No test for `processRetroActionItems` without `projectRoot`** — **Fixed:** added test.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- Bugs found and their severity:\n  - **HIGH**: `generateSlug('')` returns `''`, creating malformed TD story keys (fixed)\n  - **HIGH**: `backlogAppended` reports items as persisted when `projectRoot` is omitted (fixed)\n  - **HIGH**: `wordOverlap` exceeds 1.0 with duplicate words, breaking dedup contract (fixed)\n  - **MEDIUM**: Missing test for no-projectRoot path (fixed)\n\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed:\n  - **LOW**: `getExistingTdTitles` reconstructs titles from slugs, losing fidelity. Slug-derived words like \"registryts\" (from \"registry.ts\") happen to match because `normalizeText` also strips punctuation, but this is coincidental rather than by design. A more robust approach would store the original item text alongside the story key.\n  - **LOW**: `createTdStory` implicitly creates `epic-TD` in the epics map via spread+override even when `ensureEpicTd` wasn't called first. Works due to `?? 0` fallbacks but is a fragile coupling between the two functions.\n\n- Coverage gaps:\n  - No test for `appendToBacklogFile` when the file already exists (append-to-existing path). The test only exercises the create-new-file path.\n  - No test for error handling in `appendToBacklogFile` (e.g., permission denied on write).\n  - `state.ts` at 543 lines exceeds the project's 300-line limit (AC 10), but this is a pre-existing condition — the story only modified the `generateSprintStatusYaml` function and `parseStoryKey`, not the bulk of the file.\n\n- Architecture concerns:\n  - The story notes recommend creating `src/modules/sprint/td-state.ts` to keep TD functions isolated, but the implementation put them in `src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts` instead. This is acceptable since the functions are cohesive there, but `state.ts` remains over the 300-line budget.\n\n- Items sent back for re-development: None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story set to `verifying`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab4cae612e1e73e3f (use SendMessage with to: 'ab4cae612e1e73e3f' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68445\ntool_uses: 40\nduration_ms: 220307</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"84a01a9c-e466-45b4-91ef-8201b3712d8d","uuid":"90aa32b7-cba9-45d6-bd17-cfb11d6e5679","timestamp":"2026-03-24T22:00:15.153Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"ab4cae612e1e73e3f","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td.md\n**Issues Found:** 3 High, 1 Medium, 2 Low\n**Issues Fixed:** 3 High, 1 Medium\n**Tests Added:** 4 new tests (3657 total, all passing)\n**Coverage:** 97.1% overall, all 154 files above 80% per-file floor\n**Story Status:** verifying\n\n### HIGH Issues (all fixed)\n\n1. **H1 - `generateSlug` returns empty string for punctuation-only input** (`src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts:24-31`). Creates malformed story keys like `TD-1-` that break `nextTdStoryNumber` regex matching. **Fixed:** returns `'untitled'` as fallback.\n\n2. **H2 - `processRetroActionItems` reports `backlogAppended` items when no file was written** (`src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts:167`). When `projectRoot` is omitted, backlog items are added to the result array but never persisted. Callers believe items were appended when they weren't. **Fixed:** clears `backlogAppended` when `projectRoot` is absent.\n\n3. **H3 - `wordOverlap` returns values >1.0 with duplicate words** (`src/lib/retro-parser.ts:214-219`). Input like `['fix','fix','fix']` vs `['fix']` yielded overlap=3.0 because `filter` counted duplicates against a Set. This breaks the 0-1 contract and makes deduplication unreliable. **Fixed:** use Set on both sides before computing intersection.\n\n### MEDIUM Issues (fixed)\n\n1. **M1 - No test for `processRetroActionItems` without `projectRoot`** — **Fixed:** added test.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- Bugs found and their severity:\n  - **HIGH**: `generateSlug('')` returns `''`, creating malformed TD story keys (fixed)\n  - **HIGH**: `backlogAppended` reports items as persisted when `projectRoot` is omitted (fixed)\n  - **HIGH**: `wordOverlap` exceeds 1.0 with duplicate words, breaking dedup contract (fixed)\n  - **MEDIUM**: Missing test for no-projectRoot path (fixed)\n\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed:\n  - **LOW**: `getExistingTdTitles` reconstructs titles from slugs, losing fidelity. Slug-derived words like \"registryts\" (from \"registry.ts\") happen to match because `normalizeText` also strips punctuation, but this is coincidental rather than by design. A more robust approach would store the original item text alongside the story key.\n  - **LOW**: `createTdStory` implicitly creates `epic-TD` in the epics map via spread+override even when `ensureEpicTd` wasn't called first. Works due to `?? 0` fallbacks but is a fragile coupling between the two functions.\n\n- Coverage gaps:\n  - No test for `appendToBacklogFile` when the file already exists (append-to-existing path). The test only exercises the create-new-file path.\n  - No test for error handling in `appendToBacklogFile` (e.g., permission denied on write).\n  - `state.ts` at 543 lines exceeds the project's 300-line limit (AC 10), but this is a pre-existing condition — the story only modified the `generateSprintStatusYaml` function and `parseStoryKey`, not the bulk of the file.\n\n- Architecture concerns:\n  - The story notes recommend creating `src/modules/sprint/td-state.ts` to keep TD functions isolated, but the implementation put them in `src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts` instead. This is acceptable since the functions are cohesive there, but `state.ts` remains over the 300-line budget.\n\n- Items sent back for re-development: None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story set to `verifying`."}],"totalDurationMs":220307,"totalTokens":68445,"totalToolUseCount":40,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":391,"cache_read_input_tokens":67077,"output_tokens":976,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":391},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
